um on a particular issue, event or project.\nIn this way, blog posts suit research projects, particularly open projects and communities, because there can be frequent updates of activities and findings to bring greater attention and therefore transparency to your work.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"PJrIpRvR5t"}],"key":"A1XNrggD0z"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Starting a blog does take some investment as a web platform needs to be built and the blog needs to be frequently updated with new posts.\nIt is therefore best to share the load of this work with your team in some way or plan to get people from outside of your immediate team to write guest posts.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"fbpzTbl33W"}],"key":"U1hNl6DC3a"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to Start a Blog","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"Imn9bNwzxs"}],"label":"cm-wa-comms-blogs-start","identifier":"cm-wa-comms-blogs-start","html_id":"cm-wa-comms-blogs-start","key":"FhlykqG2F1"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Themes and Audience","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"sSUshEm46M"}],"identifier":"themes-and-audience","label":"Themes and Audience","html_id":"themes-and-audience","implicit":true,"key":"TrBN8fNVaU"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The first decision to make is to choose the theme and the audience that you want to target.\nThis will determine the readability level and overall style of your blog.","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"UMaFruUxCy"}],"key":"SNlQoAANSX"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Examples of themes include interesting research topics, a personal diary blog of your research career, a project blog to keep track of all the different aspects of the project or a community blog to help with building and maintaining the community.","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"key":"BqdBinrAqB"}],"key":"LbrXIQRRi1"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Most importantly the theme needs to have plenty of content for you to write about, be interesting to you and also engaging for others.","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"tNPhEmuQcc"}],"key":"zBYksH6COM"}],"key":"DrpL6q6sie"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Planning for Maintenance","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"brOTOtHRjE"}],"identifier":"planning-for-maintenance","label":"Planning for Maintenance","html_id":"planning-for-maintenance","implicit":true,"key":"eTsgF2kITi"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It’s always good to make a plan and try to stick to it.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"RFVuRnJzAq"}],"key":"E9DwoLFb8v"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"lis